%% Sequence: Device Enrollment (Fase 3)
%% Backoffice ↔ Assistant — enroll machine, validate, revoke
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Usuario (Backoffice)
    participant Assistant as Assistant (Electron)
    participant API as Backoffice API
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Note over User,DB: Enrollment (usuario enrola dispositivo)
    User->>API: POST /api/v1/auth/devices<br/>{ machineId, userId, osInfo }<br/>Header: Idempotency-Key
    API->>DB: findById(machineId, org)
    alt device no existe
        API->>DB: create(device)
    else device ya existe y no revocado
        API->>API: return existing (idempotent)
    end
    API-->>User: 201 { data: device }

    Note over Assistant,DB: Validación (Assistant arranca, necesita token)
    Assistant->>API: GET /api/v1/auth/devices/:machineId
    API->>DB: findByMachineId(machineId)
    alt device no existe o revocado
        API-->>Assistant: 404 / 403
    else ok
        API->>DB: updateLastSeenAt(machineId)
        API-->>Assistant: 200 { accessToken, expiresAt, organizationId, userId }
    end

    Note over User,DB: Revocación (admin)
    User->>API: DELETE /api/v1/auth/devices/:machineId<br/>Auth + Tenant + Role ADMIN
    API->>DB: revoke(machineId, orgId)
    API-->>User: 200 { data: device }
    Note over Assistant: Próxima validación fallará con 403
